\title{"mobius Path Filter"}

\taxon{skill}

\meta{description}{"Identifies tangled geodesics in proof dependency graphs via Möbius inversion."}

\subtree{
\title{Möbius Path Filter}
\p{\strong{Category}: Theorem Dependency Analysis \strong{Type}: Graph Path Classification \strong{Language}: Julia \strong{Status}: Production Ready \strong{Version}: 1.0.0 \strong{Date}: December 22, 2025}

\subtree{
\title{Overview}
\p{Identifies tangled geodesics in proof dependency graphs via Möbius inversion. Classifies paths by prime factorization to determine which dependencies are problematic (create cycles) vs. optimal (linear chains).}
}

\subtree{
\title{Key Functions}
\ul{
\li{\strong{\code{\startverb enumerate_paths(adjacency)\stopverb}}: Discovers all paths in graph}
\li{\strong{\code{\startverb factor_number(n)\stopverb}}: Prime factorization for Möbius weights}
\li{\strong{\code{\startverb mobius_weight(n)\stopverb}}: Computes μ(n) ∈ {-1, 0, +1}}
\li{\strong{\code{\startverb filter_tangled_paths(adjacency)\stopverb}}: Identifies problem paths}
\li{\strong{\code{\startverb generate_filter_report()\stopverb}}: Human-readable analysis}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Mathematical Foundation}
\p{\strong{Möbius Inversion for Path Classification}}

\pre{\startverb
μ(n) = +1   : prime paths (keep - linear chains)
μ(n) = -1   : odd-composite paths (rewrite needed)
μ(n) = 0    : squared-factors (remove - redundant)
\stopverb}

\p{Uses prime factorization to weight geodesic paths in dependency graph. Helps identify which theorems create circular dependencies that impede spectral gap.}
}

\subtree{
\title{Usage}
\pre{\startverb
using MobiusFilter

# Analyze proof dependencies
prime_paths, tangled = filter_tangled_paths(adjacency)

# Get recommendations
report = generate_filter_report(adjacency)
println(report)
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Integration Points}
\ul{
\li{Diagnosis tool for Week 2 analysis phase}
\li{Feeds into safe_rewriting_advisor for remediation}
\li{Used by continuous-inverter for automated detection}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Performance}
\ul{
\li{Execution time: ~1 second (for 5-node test graphs)}
\li{Path enumeration: Exponential but capped by practical graph size}
\li{Prime factorization: O(√n) per path}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{References}
\ul{
\li{Hardy & Wright (1979): Elementary Number Theory}
\li{Möbius inversion theory for discrete mathematics}
}
}
}